track_notes: Like on G/TW-001 you use part of A Wainwrights Coast to Coast path which is also the Cleveland Way National Trail here. There is roadside parking. The Lord Stones Country Park with Cafe has reopened (winter 2013) and gone upmarket. They have their own car park for patrons if you use the facilities before or after the activation.
track_title: G/TW-002 Cringle Moor (Drake Howe) from Lord Stones

track_notes: A walk from Lord Stones Car Park. Missed the Cairn at the highest point due to rain and clag with visibility down to 20/30 yards and had to backtrack. On the up side, Lord Stones has now re-opened after a refurbishment to a very high standard.
